2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
28 g Spring Mix
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 unit(s) Tomato
6 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
1 unit(s) Lemon
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
2 unit(s) Russet Potato
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Butter*
0.38 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*

Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add potatoes and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, tossing halfway through, until golden-brown and tender, 25-28 min.

Meanwhile, zest, then juice lemon.
Cut tomato into 1/2-inch slices.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When the pan is hot, add Beyond Meat® patties. Pan-fry until cooked through, 4-5 min per side.**

Meanwhile, halve buns, then arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up.
Toast in the top of the oven until lightly golden, 2-3 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on buns so they don't burn.)

Meanwhile, add feta, yogurt sauce and lemon juice to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add potatoes, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, lemon zest and Zesty Garlic Blend to another medium bowl. Toss to coat.
Spread 1 tbsp feta-yogurt sauce over bottom buns, then stack with spring mix, Beyond Meat® patties and tomatoes. Close with top buns.
Divide burgers, zesty lemon potatoes between plates.
Serve remaining feta-yogurt sauce on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, skip the instructions to form the patties. Reserve panko for another use. Use all the Zesty garlic blend for potatoes in step 6. Cook Beyond Meat® patties the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the pork.**